title: (SOLVED) 820-3209 no power
message:
Ivy Bridge CPU has very low values as normal.

If board stays on in SMC bypass mode, there is a problem with SMC some I/V sensor (pages 45/46).
Start checking SMC_DCIN/PBUS_VSENSE and SMC_DCIN/BMON_ISENSE.

Post U7400 voltages; pins 40, 24, 15, 2, 1.

title: (SOLVED) 820-3209 no power
message:
this solved. found short on C1754 PP1V5_S3RS0 after this cap removed unable to supply 1.5V
checked r7850 on pin 1 PP1V5_S3RS0_FET_R is 1.5V pin 2 is 0.3v. i just jumper R7850 in order to supply 1.5V to PP1V5_S3RS0
thanks!
